# Vivaldi Features 👀
This post is about the interesting features of the [Vivaldi browser](https://vivaldi.com). A great browser for research. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Grouping Tabs

Split screens. This is the number 1 feature of this browser that I like.

1. Tab Stack
2. Tab Tiling

See [here](https://help.vivaldi.com/guide/quick-start/#pk_campaign=sd&pk_kwd=get-started) for info.

### Save sessions

Once you have grouped tabs together, you can save sessions by right clicking the tab stack.

## Web Panel

Shows mobile versions of any website on the sidebar. Good for checking new messages.

## F2

Shortcut for commands.

## Notes

Open a new tab and click on "Notes".

### Links

You can use the `[link](address)` syntax as you would in Markdown.

### Emojis

You can use **\[Win key + . \]** to see emojis. 😍
